We further carried out HRTEM to investigate lattice registration at the nanotube/nanosheet interface. Considering that ultrathin nanosheets randomly grow around the nanotubes in a hierarchical manner, we cross-sectioned the unidirectionally aligned nanowires to observe them along different directions. HRTEM images on the nanotubes, nanosheets, and tube/sheet interfaces show lattice spacing of 0.305 nm, which we index to the (015) plane of BiSeTe ternary compounds (Fig. 1d–o). FFTs obtained from these HRTEM images indicate a single diffraction pattern assigned to the [1¯00\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
